headline.main: SPY RING EVIDENCE GOES TO GRAND JURY; Jane Term of Inquiry Body Is Extended Through July

lead_paragraph: The presentation of evidence against the alleged espionage ring broken up by the Federal Bureau of Investigation Sunday began yesterday before the Federal grand jury in Brooklyn. United States Attorney Harold M. Kennedy disclosed that the June term of the grand jury had been extended through July so that it might hear the case.
abstract: evidence goes to Bklyn Fed grand jury; NMU suspends 2 members who pleaded guilty; defers action on 5 other members
